If dp[z][0] is true, then combining it with j would allow us to set dp[z | j][1] to true. So the line should be:

if ( dp[z][0] )

Because if the current state z is achievable (from previous friends), then adding the current friend's coverage j (the mask of friends he can carry) would result in the union of z and j being achievable. So for each z, if dp[z][0] is true, then set dp[z | j][1] to true. So the missing code is replacing the comment with dp[z][0], which checks if the previous state z is reachable.
